courses.duties:
Inverted-classroom and Office Hours TA:
Attend lectures to assist in classroom activities. Prepare for each week by doing online programming activities.  Hold office hours. Mark exams. May include other tasks, such as monitoring discussion forums.

Office Hours and Marking TA:
Hold office hours. Prepare for office hours by reviewing assignments and other course materials. Mark tests and exams. May include other tasks, such as monitoring discussion forums.
courses.qualifications:
Inverted-classroom and Office Hours TA:
Experience with programming, such as by completing a 200-level CSC course, or by achieving excellent marks in multiple 100-level CSC courses, or equivalent. Experience with Python, at the level of CSC 148 or equivalent. Must be enrolled in or have completed a computer science degree, or equivalent. Must be interested in teaching beginner programmers. Willing to try different approaches when explaining simple concepts. TAs should be available during at least one of the CSC 108 lecture times (MWF10-11, MWF11-12, MWF1-2, MWF2-3, W6-9). TAs should have some availability Monday to Friday, 9am to 5pm for office hours and marking.

Office Hours and Marking TA:
Experience with programming, such as by completing a 200-level CSC course, or by achieving excellent marks in multiple 100-level CSC courses, or equivalent. Experience with Python, at the level of CSC 148 or equivalent. Must be enrolled in or have completed a computer science degree, or equivalent. Must be interested in teaching beginner programmers. TAs should have some availability Monday to Friday, 9am to 5pm for office hours and marking.
